quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  16,90,"Verily, Allah commands justice, the doing of good (kindness, benevolence), and liberality to kindred, and He forbids all shameful deeds (lewdness, abomination, perversity) and wickedness (wrong, injustice, oppression, rebellion); He exhorts you that per c"
  16,91,"Fulfil the Covenant of Allah when you have entered into it, and break not your oaths after confirming them, for you thereby make Allah your surety; verily, Allah knows what you do"
  16,92,"And be not like her who unravels her yarn, fraying it out after she hath spun it close, by taking your oaths for mutual intrigue, because one nation is more numerous than another; Allah only tries you therewith, but He will make manifest to you on the Day"
  16,93,"But had Allah pleased He would have made you one nation; but He leads astray whom He will, and guides whom He will; - but you shall be questioned as to that which you used to do"
  16,94,"Take not therefore your oaths for mutual deceit, lest a foot slip after being planted firmly, and you taste of evil in that you turned folks off the path of Allah, and your s should be a mighty doom"
  16,95,"And sell not the Covenant of Allah for a little price; Verily, with Allah alone is that which is better for you, if you did but know"
  16,96,"What you have is spent (wastes away), but what Allah has endures; and verily, We will recompense the patient (steadfast) in proportion to the best of what they used to do"
  16,97,"Whoever acts aright, male or female, and is a believer, We will quicken with a goodly life; and We will recompense them in proportion to the best of what they used to do"
  16,98,When you do read the Quran ask refuge with Allah from Satan the outcast (the rejected or pelted one)
  16,99,"Verily, he has no power over those who believe and who upon their Lord rely (trust)"
  16,100,"His power is only over those who take him for a patron, and over the idolaters"
  16,101,"And whenever We change one revelation for another - Allah knows best what He reveals (sends down) - They say, \"You are but inventing!\"- Nay, most of them know not"
  16,102,"Say, \"The Holy Spirit brought it down from your Lord in truth, that it may confirm (the faith of) those who believe, and for a guidance and glad tidings to those who have Surrendered unto Allah (Muslims)"
  16,103,"We know well that they say, \"It is only some mortal who teaches him.\" But the tongue of him they point to (Muhammad) is outlandish, while this (Quran) is Arabic, pure and clear"
  16,104,"Verily, those who believe not in Allah´s signs, Allah will not guide them, and for them is grievous woe"
  16,105,"Only they are the inventors who believe not in Allah´s signs; and these, they are the liars"
  16,106,"Whoever disbelieves in Allah after having believed - unless it be one who is forced and whose heart is still content in the faith - but whoever expands his breast to (easing) disbelieve - on them is wrath from Allah, and theirs is a mighty doom"
  16,107,"That is because they preferred the love of the life of this world to the Hereafter, and because Allah guides not unbelieving people"
  16,108,"These are they whose heart, and hearing, and sight, Allah has sealed, and these, they are the heedless"
  16,109,"Assuredly, in the Hereafter they will be the losers"
  16,110,"Then, verily, your Lord - to those who fled after they had been tried, and then fought strenuously and were patient, - verily, your Lord after that will be Forgiving and Merciful"